[3] Cholera - Nigeria (Borno State)
Date: Mon 15 Oct 2018
Source: Reliefweb, a Government of Nigeria report [edited]
https://reliefweb.int/report/nigeria/situation-report-cholera-outbreak-borno-state-no-40-15-october-2018


Situation Report of Cholera Outbreak in Borno State No. 40: 15 Oct 2018
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Highlights:
- 89 additional suspected cases of cholera were reported on [15 Oct 2018] in Borno State
- No new death was reported

Epidemiological Summary:
The total number of suspected cholera cases reported as of [15 Oct 2018] stands at 4942 with 71 associated deaths, (CFR - 1.43%). Cases: 1956 in Jere, 1003 in MMC, 339 in Magumeri, 34 in Kaga, 130 in Konduga, 136 in Chibok, 11 in Shani, 42 in Damboa, 960 in Ngala, 66 in Askira-Uba, 159 in Kwaya-Kusar, 53 in Bama and 53 in Dikwa LGAs. No additional case reported from Kaga, Chibok, Shani, Damboa and Kwaya-Kusar LGAs.

Out of the 169 samples collected and tested in the State using RDTs, 136 (80%) were positive while 33 (37%) of 88 samples were culture positive.

